<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Bars 0-4 (phrase A): D-A7-D-A oscillation with G and Em passing chords
  A7 voicings include G natural (7th) for color
- Bars 5-8 (repeat A): D 2nd inversion, G 1st inv, Em7 — varied inversions
- Bars 9-10 (bridge): High register D-A-Em-A motion; Bm7 adds color
- Bars 11-14 (coda): D-G-Bm descending bass, final Bm-A7-D cadence

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 1→2: D bass D2 steps up to G2 (G chord) — ascending bass line
- Bar 3: C#° substitutes G#° — C#3-G3-C#4 creates leading-tone tension
- Bar 10: Bm7 uses B2-F#3-A3-D4 — the A (7th) adds color without muddiness
- Bar 14: Bm→A7→D final cadence: vi-V7-I with smooth F#3→E3→F#3 motion in LH

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup: single note
- Bars 1-4: per-beat chords, 2+4 texture, light
- Bars 5-8: richer with inversions, 3-note RH starts appearing
- Bars 9-12: climax, high melody D5, C#5 — maximum voicing density
- Bars 13-14: settling descent, final D in root position
-->
